<h3 id="the-fix">The Fix</h3>

<p>
  After a bit of duck hunting I found that i was not the 
  only one to have experienced this issue.
  Thanks to this {{ link::e(path="https://forums.lenovo.com/t5/Gaming-Laptops/Y520-Screen-flashing-colors-at-start-up/m-p/4164933?page=2#5303052", description="forum post") }}
  I discovered that the Lenovo P14s has an 
  {{ text::emphasize(text="emergency reset hole") }}. The hole is on the underside of 
  the laptop above the centre screw.
</p>
{{ image::boxed(path=
  "blog/lenovo-p14s-red-blue-green-white-black-flashing-screen/lenovo-p14s-rear.png", 
  width="600px") 
}}
<p>
  Using a paperclip or similar (I used a small allen key)
  depress the button for 15 seconds. After that, power on 
  the laptop. 
</p>
<p>
  The laptop booted into recovery mode, I then just clicked 
  on the restart computer option. The laptop then booted 
  normally. Crisis averted.
</p>

<h3 id="outro">Outro</h3>
<p>
  In case of emergency, press the emergency hole.
</p>
<p>
  <i>I am Jack's smirking revenge.</i>
</p>
